garden-rumor/articleshow/132147833.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/is-kai-cenat-set-to-stream-taylor-swift-and-travis-kelces-wedding-truth-behind-the-madison-square-garden-rumor/articleshow/132147833.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T02:28:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132147830,imgsize-913571.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Religious proverb of the day from Thailand: "Paste gold leaf onto the back of a Buddha statue" inspires us to do good when no one is watching]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132147688.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/religious-proverb-of-the-day-from-thailand-paste-gold-leaf-onto-the-back-of-a-buddha-statue-inspires-us-to-do-good-when-no-one-is-watching/articleshow/132147688.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/religious-proverb-of-the-day-from-thailand-paste-gold-leaf-onto-the-back-of-a-buddha-statue-inspires-us-to-do-good-when-no-one-is-watching/articleshow/132147688.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T01:32:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132147701,imgsize-217618.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Latin proverb of the day: 'Let the experiment be made on a low-value body']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132146711.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A historical Latin phrase, "fiat experimentum in corpore vili," meaning "let the experiment be made on a low-value body," reveals a troubling past where scientific discovery prioritized knowledge over human dignity. Though explicitly rejected today, its legacy echoes in modern debates about risk distribution in research and medicine, forcing us to confront how progress is achieved and who bears its cost.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/latin-proverb-of-the-day-let-the-experiment-be-made-on-a-low-value-body-a-chilling-glimpse-into-early-science-and-ethics-debates-that-still-echo-today/articleshow/132146711.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/latin-proverb-of-the-day-let-the-experiment-be-made-on-a-low-value-body-a-chilling-glimpse-into-early-science-and-ethics-debates-that-still-echo-today/articleshow/132146711.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T00:58:45+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132147389,imgsize-1172967.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Beijing pushes for a China-Pakistan-style economic corridor with Bangladesh and Myanmar]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132147160.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[China is pushing for an economic corridor linking Bangladesh and Myanmar, mirroring CPEC's strategic importance. This initiative, discussed during Bangladesh PM Tarique Rahman's China visit, aims to boost connectivity, with China developing the Mongla port. Beijing has also expressed openness to other nations joining this "transnational initiative," which has drawn India's attention due to its proximity to the eastern border.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/beijing-pushes-for-a-china-pakistan-style-eco-corridor-with-bangladesh-and-myanmar/articleshow/132147160.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/beijing-pushes-for-a-china-pakistan-style-eco-corridor-with-bangladesh-and-myanmar/articleshow/132147160.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T00:53:11+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Ahsan Tasnim</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132147115,imgsize-685206.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Being American means nothing: MAGA influencer slams children of H-1B standing in front of a Hindu temple ahead of July 4]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132146522.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/being-american-means-nothing-maga-influencer-slams-children-of-h-1b-standing-in-front-of-a-hindu-temple-ahead-of-july-4/articleshow/132146522.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/being-american-means-nothing-maga-influencer-slams-children-of-h-1b-standing-in-front-of-a-hindu-temple-ahead-of-july-4/articleshow/132146522.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T00:42:15+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132146713,imgsize-113960.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Arabic proverb of the day: 'The monkey is a gazelle in its mother's eyes']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132146160.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An enchanting Arabic proverb states, 'The monkey is a gazelle in its mother's eyes,' capturing the idea that love significantly impacts how we perceive others. This adage, rooted in oral heritage, emphasizes that parents often view their children with a loving bias, making it easy to overlook their shortcomings. The vivid metaphor suggests that emotional connections can cloud our judgments, a notion reflected in contemporary psychological studies.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/arabic-proverb-of-the-day-the-monkey-is-a-gazelle-in-its-mothers-eyesa-saying-about-parental-love-and-how-affection-shapes-perception-across-cultures/articleshow/132146160.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/arabic-proverb-of-the-day-the-monkey-is-a-gazelle-in-its-mothers-eyesa-saying-about-parental-love-and-how-affection-shapes-perception-across-cultures/articleshow/132146160.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-03T00:40:34+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132146671,imgsize-171040.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian-origin man convicted of stabbing wife in Canada; claimed he accidentally ‘poked’ her]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132144921.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Jagpreet Singh, an Indian national, has been sentenced for second-degree murder after fatally stabbing his wife, Balwinder Kaur, only six days post-arrival in Canada. The court rejected Singh's assertion that the stabbing was accidental during a dispute, labeling his testimony as untrustworthy. Previously married for twenty years, Kaur had sponsored Singh's visa, and the tragic event took place on March 15, 2024, after she expressed concerns about his arrival.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indian-origin-jagpreet-singh-convicted-of-murdering-wife-in-canada-claimed-he-accidentally-poked-her-with-a-knife/articleshow/132144921.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indian-origin-jagpreet-singh-convicted-of-murd